<!-- Account Guardian — FAQ -->
<section class="faq-section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <span class="eyebrow-tag">FAQ</span>
    <h2 class="section-headline centered">Common questions, straight answers.</h2>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          Does Account Guardian make changes to my Stripe account?
          <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>No. We have read-only access to your Stripe data. We read your signals and send you alerts — we never change anything, adjust settings, or touch your money.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          How quickly will I know if something is wrong?
          <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>We check your signals daily. If a threshold is crossed, you'll receive an alert the same day — before Stripe acts. In most cases, you'll know 2–4 weeks before Stripe would typically escalate.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          What exactly are the 5 risk signals you monitor?
          <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>We monitor: dispute rate, refund rate, chargeback rate, revenue trend, and Stripe's internal risk flags. These are the signals Stripe uses to evaluate account health — we surface them to you before Stripe acts on them.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          What do the alerts actually look like?
          <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Specific, actionable alerts like: "Your chargeback rate hit 2.1% — above Stripe's 1% threshold. Here's exactly what to do to bring it down." Not "something looks off." Real numbers, specific guidance, next steps.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          What happens after the 14-day trial?
          <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Your trial ends with no credit card on file. If you want to continue, you subscribe at $79/month. If you don't, you lose access — no charges, no hassle.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          Is my Stripe data secure?
          <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Yes. We use read-only Stripe API access — we can never write to your account or move money. Data is encrypted in transit and at rest. We don't share your data with third parties, ever.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          Can I cancel anytime?
          <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Yes. Month-to-month, no contracts. Cancel from your dashboard in 30 seconds. No penalties, no questions asked.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
function toggleFaq(btn) {
  const answer = btn.nextElementSibling;
  const isOpen = answer.classList.contains('open');
  document.querySelectorAll('.faq-answer').forEach(a => a.classList.remove('open'));
  document.querySelectorAll('.faq-icon').forEach(i => i.textContent = '+');
  if (!isOpen) {
    answer.classList.add('open');
    btn.querySelector('.faq-icon').textContent = '−';
  }
}
</script>